      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-03-31T20:35:50Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Expresses the sense of the House of Representatives that, in order to meet our nation's long-term energy demands, any comprehensive energy bill must address specific aspects, including: (1) encouraging technological innovations to exploit our vast supply of natural gas; (2) increasing our domestic oil production, infrastructure, and refining capacity; (3) exploring and investing in the current nuclear fleet and advanced reactor technologies; (4)taking advantage of our domestic coal supply; (5) using expanded renewable and alternative energy sources; and (6) promoting increased conservation and energy efficiency.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-03-10T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
